    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="355"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AA/3–2851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Indonesia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 28, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1052. Usgoc 499. Re secretariat. As stated previously (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1"
                        >Gocus</gloss> 497) [<hi rend="italic">Usgoc 497</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d355fn1">Not printed, but see paragraph 3 of telegram 1309
                        from Djakarta, March 26, and footnote 2 thereto, <ref target="#pg_627">p
                            627</ref>.</note>] we do not believe it necessary secretariat remain,
                    but under <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> procedures final decision such
                    matters rests with <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>.</p>
                <p>We will advise him that so far as we can now foresee Comm will not be active in
                    future and suggest that he might wish to take this situation into account in
                    planning administrative arrangements when Comm does adjourn <hi rend="italic"
                        >sine die</hi>.</p>
                <p>Re suggestion that <gloss target="#t_UNTA1">UNTA</gloss> Mission secretariat take
                    over <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> secretariat functions. While we do
                    not believe this practice of double responsibilities desirable believe this
                    question one for secretariat NY decide and if they have no objections this
                    solution, we wld acquiesce.</p>
                <p>Sent to AmEmbassy Djakarta 1052; rptd info AmEmbassy Brussels 1286, Canberra 259,
                    The Hague 1108, <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> New York for action as
                    indicated 821.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
